reviews.text:
Plenty of food on the wedding menu.
I was attending my cousins wedding banquet set for 10 tables and the food was very good. 

The environment was also very nice but the staff seemed to be unknowledgeable of some areas of the hotel. 

The perfume or air freshener in the hotel was strong.   A bit more than to my liking.

Other than that, the venue had a nice decor, the staff were friendly and they even helped us with some take away of some of their dishes as there was just too much food on the menu.

Thank you Rosewood for the amazing afternoon! Just came for lunch and was a bit lost, Vittorio D showed me the way to the Holts Cafe and gave me a recommendation to try the cheesecake with blueberries. I had also been craving a fresh salad and Chef Fernando so graciously made a special order for me due to my food allergies. Overall, their warm hospitality is the reason I'll be frequenting Rosewood in the future.

Beautiful rooms, its still new so relatively quiet. But smaller than the normal rooms, the standard rooms do not offer breakfast. But they have a cocktail/jazz bar next door and a fabulous restaurant.
At Darkside the bar. Great decor and ambience. Excellent jazz musicians and singer. Drink selection is good. Most aren't cheap since Rosewood is a 6-star hotel

Five of us went for high tea at the Butterfly Room. The building is impressive and the Butterfly Room is very attractively decorated. The afternoon tea was nice but not splendid as you might expect from a self proclaimed 6 star hotel. The scones were quite hard but when I pointed this out to the waitress she said "this is our Chef's style". Some of the cakes are too unorthodox that all our group agreed it was weird. The waiting staff asked what we thought about the food. Politely I told them I thought it was "so-so" and their reply was "the hotel has only just opened and we will look to improve". I'm sorry but for a 5 star (sorry 6 star) hotel you need to be brilliant from day 1. No excuses.

The worst thing however about our experience is the lack of coordination and knowledge between the staff. When I made the reservation I asked about parking and was informed they had a parking garage on site. However when we arrived at the hotel we were informed there was no parking. I clarified if this meant the parking garage was full or was just available for hotel guests but was told "we have no parking here". So we parked away from the hotel and walked. The same thing happened to our guests too. When we finished our high tea and paid the bill I was asked if we had a car parked at the hotel as there was free parking allowance for restaurant guests. I was shocked to hear this considering we had been turned away earlier. When I queried this with the Manager at the Butterfly Room I was told they do have a several storey car park at the hotel but then given the excuse that the hotel does has over 200 workers and they are still learning everything. On our way back down I again asked in the lobby about parking and was told there wasn't any at this location. So either staff are not trained properly or they are lying, neither of which is acceptable for a high-end hotel.

The hotel seems to have good reviews so far from staying guests so I am assuming that the hotel are putting all their focus on them. Other guests to the hotel seem to not be a priority. That needs to change if I am to consider going back.

reviews.text: 五星級新酒店 ， 剛開業幾個月， 位於尖沙咀 遊客區 星光大道旁， 臨海一邊 可看到維多利亞港及香港島景色。前 泰國總理 " 他信 " 嫁女， 也選址在這裏設宴。

都幾貴，但質數不及福臨門或唐宮，由於坐位小，訂枱要等很長時間。窗外景色很美。整個维港景都可看到。藉得一讚。Service 都不錯。人手不太夠。
